-- ECB’s Costa Says Portugal Is on the Right Path, Meeting Targets
-- B y   H e n r i q u e   A l m e i d a
-- 2012-10-10T09:22:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-10/ecb-s-costa-says-portugal-is-on-the-right-path-meeting-targets.html
European Central Bank Governing
Council member Carlos Costa said  Portugal ’s adjustment effort is
on a “good path” as the country’s government continues to meet
its bailout targets.  “The effort of adjusting the  Portuguese economy  has been
considerable,” Costa, who also heads the Bank of Portugal, said
in a speech at a conference in Macau that was posted on the
central bank’s website today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Henrique Almeida in Lisbon at 
 halmeida5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
